.TH HSH 1 2025-01-02 GNU Simple Shell User Manual

.SH NAME
.B hsh \- Simple UNIX command-line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B ./hsh [command] [options]

.SH DESCRIPTION
hsh is a custom UNIX command-line interpreter that reads and executes commands
from the standard input or from a file. It's functionality is limited to the
built-in commands 'env' and 'exit' and those found in the global environment
variable $PATH.
hsh was developed on Ubuntu 20.04 ITS and compiled with gcc version 11.40. 

.SH INVOCATION
hsh can be used in both interaction and non-interactive mode:

.IP Interactive mode
To invoke hsh in interactive mode run the executable file using -./hsh.
Commands can then be input directly into the command line using the 
following syntax:

[command][flag][argument]

.IP Non-interactive mode
To invoke hsh non-interactively, use the following syntax:

[command][flag][argument] | ./hsh

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
hsh supports the following built-in commands:

.IP exit
- Exits the program.

.IP env
- Prints the current environment. 

.SH SEE ALSO
bash(1), sh(1)

.SH BUGS
No known bugs.
If bugs found please contact the authors. 

